theorem Topology.P3_iInter_closed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {ι : Sort*}
    {A : ι → Set X} :
    (∀ i, IsClosed (A i)) →
    (∀ i, Topology.P3 (A i)) →
    Topology.P3 (⋂ i, A i) := by
  intro hClosed hP3
  -- From `P3` and closedness we infer that each `A i` is open.
  have hOpen : ∀ i, IsOpen (A i) := by
    intro i
    exact
      (Topology.P3_iff_isOpen_of_isClosed (A := A i) (hClosed i)).1 (hP3 i)
  -- The intersection of (arbitrarily many) open sets is open.
  have hOpen_iInter : IsOpen (⋂ i, A i) := by
    apply isOpen_iInter
    intro i
    exact hOpen i
  -- Any open set satisfies `P3`.
  exact Topology.P3_of_isOpen (A := ⋂ i, A i) hOpen_iInter

theorem Topology.P3_of_dense {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense A → Topology.P3 A := by
  intro hA
  have hclosure : closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa using hA.closure_eq
  exact Topology.P3_of_closure_eq_univ (A := A) hclosure

theorem Topology.interior_union_eq_self_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen A) (hB : IsOpen B) :
    interior (A ∪ B) = A ∪ B := by
  have hOpen : IsOpen (A ∪ B) := hA.union hB
  simpa using hOpen.interior_eq
